What You Actually Have
Project 1 — DPAH (this project)

Full RBAC, LDAP auth, JWT, role-based agents
Workflow-driven (RMS timesheet, HRMS leave, MRR)
Structured outputs — forms, approvals, DB writes
Users are internal employees with defined roles

Project 2 — Agentic AI Dashboard

No real RBAC
Dynamic — user asks a question, LLM writes code, generates graphs/tables on the fly
Excel data stored in ChromaDB (as a data store, not for vector search)
Server-side dataframe kept in memory per collection
Output is visual analytics — charts, tables, computed results

These are fundamentally different tools serving different purposes:

DPAH is a workflow automation tool — structured, auditable, role-gated
Agentic Dashboard is an analytics exploration tool — dynamic, open-ended, visual


Same server → no CORS, no domain issues
Both apps have their own sidebar → iframe won't work (nested sidebars = terrible UX)
Collection access is department-based, not individual → RBAC bridge is simple
You want Option A → minimal changes, fast delivery

Not an iframe. Full page navigation to the agentic dashboard, user lands already authenticated. Feels like one platform because the navigation is seamless. Each app keeps its own sidebar and layout.